From: Nicholas D Steeves <nsteeves@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 3 Mar 2018 19:27:31 -0500
Subject: Disable one consistently failing test

Forwarded: https://github.com/jorgenschaefer/elpy/issues/1308
Last-Update: 2020-11-18

1 unexpected results:
FAILED elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-should-notify-of-removing-main

It may be possible to make
elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-should-notify-of-removing-main
pass by packaging ert-runner and then somehow integrating it with
dh-elpa.  That is to say, this test seems to depend on assumptions
associated with a Cask+ert-runner self-test infrastructure.

As far as I can tell ert-runner--like Cask--is a tool that is
incompatible with dh-elpa and it should be similarly bypassed and not
depended on as a build dependency.  See bug #837922 and the Debian
Emacsen Team's wiki for more information.
---
 test/elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-test.el | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/test/elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-test.el b/test/elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-test.el
index dd8a6d2..080430b 100644
--- a/test/elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-test.el
+++ b/test/elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-test.el
@@ -53,6 +53,7 @@
                         (get-buffer "*Python*"))))))
 
 (ert-deftest elpy-shell-send-region-or-buffer-should-notify-of-removing-main ()
+  (ert-skip "Skipping, because this test requires ert-runner")
   (elpy-testcase ()
     (elpy-enable)
     (python-mode)
